HEADWORD: Glac
<hw>Gla`c⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., p.p. of
<ets>glacer</ets> to freeze, to ice. Cf. <er>Glacier</er>.]</ety>
<def>Smoothly coated with icing or crystals of sugar; iced; glazed; --
said of fruits, sweetmeats, cake, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> candied, crystalized, glac⟦eacute⟧ed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glacial</ent>⟦br⟧
